#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:55
msgid "**OP_ADD** = **0** --- Sums two numbers using ``a + b``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:57
msgid "**OP_SUB** = **1** --- Subtracts two numbers using ``a - b``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:59
msgid "**OP_MUL** = **2** --- Multiplies two numbers using ``a * b``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:61
msgid "**OP_DIV** = **3** --- Divides two numbers using ``a / b``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:63
msgid ""
"**OP_MOD** = **4** --- Calculates the remainder of two numbers. "
"Translates to ``mod(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:65
msgid ""
"**OP_POW** = **5** --- Raises the ``a`` to the power of ``b``. Translates"
" to ``pow(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:67
msgid ""
"**OP_MAX** = **6** --- Returns the greater of two numbers. Translates to "
"``max(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:69
msgid ""
"**OP_MIN** = **7** --- Returns the lesser of two numbers. Translates to "
"``min(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:71
msgid ""
"**OP_ATAN2** = **8** --- Returns the arc-tangent of the parameters. "
"Translates to ``atan(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodefloatop.rst:73
msgid ""
"**OP_STEP** = **9** --- Generates a step function by comparing ``b``\\ "
"(x) to ``a``\\ (edge). Returns 0.0 if ``x`` is smaller than ``edge`` and "
"otherwise 1.0. Translates to ``step(a, b)`` in the Godot Shader Language."
msgstr ""

